National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Dr. Ibrahim Kalin, Spokesperson and Chief Advisor to the President of Turkey, in Istanbul. They discussed their support for Ukraine in the face of Russia's aggression, condemning Russia's attempted annexation of Ukrainian territory. Sullivan appreciated Turkey's efforts to improve global food security by facilitating the export of Ukrainian grain and their diplomatic work to secure the release of Ukrainian prisoners of war and two American citizens held by Russia. They also discussed regional security issues, including support for peace negotiations between Armenia and Azerbaijan, the importance of dialogue and diplomacy to resolve disagreements in the Eastern Mediterranean, and progress on NATO accession for Finland and Sweden.